    <title type="text">Herzfeld at Samarra</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[The Smithsonian Institution's <a
      href="http://collections.si.edu/">Collections Search Center</a> announced on their
      <a
      href="http://si-siris.blogspot.com/2011/01/100th-anniversary-of-samarra-excavation.html">blog</a>
      this morning the launch of a new<br /><br /><a
      href="http://www.asia.si.edu/research/archivesSamarra.asp">Samarra Resource
      Page</a><br /><blockquote><span style="font-size: x-small;">Ernst
      Herzfeld’s archaeological excavation of <a
      href="http://collections.si.edu/search/results.jsp?view=&amp;date.slider=&amp;q=Samarra&amp;dsort=&amp;fq=name:%22Herzfeld%2C+Ernst%22">Samarra</a>&nbsp;
      will mark its 100th anniversary in 2011.&nbsp; To honor the occasion, the&nbsp;
      Freer|Sackler Archives has created the Samarra Resource Page that&nbsp; collates
      collections online content, social media content, and related&nbsp; scholarly content, to
      provide an easy central resource for all of the&nbsp; Herzfeld paper materials and
      products.&nbsp; Preservation, digitization, and&nbsp; cataloging have been made
      possible by the Leon Levy Foundation.</span> </blockquote><div class="post-body
      entry-content"><a
      href="http://sirismm.si.edu/sackler/herzfeld_bib/fsa_a.6_04/FSA_A.6_04.20.119.jpg"
      style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img alt="Excavation of Sāmarrāʼ (Iraq):
      View of the Qaṣr al-ʿĀshiq towards the North, 1911-1913 [graphic]. Ernst Herzfeld Papers,
      Freer|Sackler Archives." border="0" height="195"
      src="http://sirismm.si.edu/sackler/herzfeld_bib/fsa_a.6_04/FSA_A.6_04.20.119.jpg"
      title="Excavation of Sāmarrāʼ (Iraq): View of the Qaṣr al-ʿĀshiq towards the North, 1911-1913
      [graphic]. Ernst Herzfeld Papers, Freer|Sackler Archives." width="640" /></a><br
      /><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><br /><span style="font-size:
      xx-small;"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Above Image:
      </span><a class="boldBlackFont2"
      href="http://siris-archives.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&amp;profile=all&amp;source=%7E%21siarchives&amp;uri=full=3100001%7E%21293357%7E%210#focus"
      style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Excavation of Sāmarrāʼ (Iraq): View of the
      Qaṣr al-ʿĀshiq towards the North, 1911-1913 [graphic].</a><span style="font-family:
      Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp; </span></span>
      </div></div><br />And see also&nbsp; AWOL's entry <a
      href="http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2010/08/erst-herzfeld-papers.html">Ernst
      Herzfeld Papers</a><br /><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><a
      href="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/894082">Samarra in Pleiades
      http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/894082</a> </div>]]></content>
